⚙️ Step-by-Step: BTT Eddy USB Setup & Calibration for Sovol SV08 (Mainline Klipper) // https://youtu.be/xnGhGZesipI?si=ITTud6lQNlf95Gel

1. Connect via SSH and ensure you’re on Mainline Klipper:cd ~/klipper && git checkout master
2. With kiauh update all (min version v0.13.0-641)
3. Install katapult in BTT Eddy (https://github.com/Rappetor/katapult-on-btt-eddy)
4. Power off your BTT Eddy (e.g. pulling the USB plug, turning off the printer etc.)
5. Press and hold the little boot button on top of the BTT Eddy and power up the BTT Eddy (e.g. plugging the USB cable back in or turning the printer back on etc.)
6. Once powered on wait a few seconds and you can release the button again, it should now be in boot/DFU mode.
7. Check if BTT Eddy is in boot mode with: lsusb

It should look something like this:

	ID: 2e8a:0003 Raspberry Pi RP2 Boot

8. Now we are going to configure, build and flash the Katapult firmware for the BTT Eddy.

cd ~/katapult && make menuconfig KCONFIG_CONFIG=eddy

Configure the Katapult firmware as shown in the screenshot (Eddy_Katapult_Menuconfig.jpg) . Press [Q] to quit and save changes.

